tos</i> ‘Christ’ + <i>pherein</i> ‘to bear’. This was popular among early Christians, conscious of the fact that they were metaphorically bearing Christ in their hearts. A later, over-literal interpretation of the name gave rise to the legend of a saint who actually bore the Christ-child over a stream; he is regarded as the patron of travellers. In England the name was uncommon in the Middle Ages, but became very popular in the 16th century, especially in parts of the North."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Katherine de Buckfold was born in 1355, in England as the daughter of de Buckfold. She had at least 1 son with Sir John Beale. She died in 1380, in Glassenbury, Kent, England, at the age of 25."},"et":{"1355–1380":"1355–1380","1340–1399":"1340–1399","1375–1429":"1375–1429","–Male":"Surnud","2 April 1375":"2. aprill 1375","1355":"1355","1399":"1399","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","1380":"1380","1429":"1429","Glassenbury, Kent, England":"Glassenbury, Kent, England","Maidstone, Kent, England":"Maidstone, Kent, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"1355–1380":"1355–1380","1340–1399":"1340–1399","1375–1429":"1375–1429","–Male":"Kuollut","2 April 1375":"2. huhtikuuta 1375","1355":"1355","1399":"1399","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","1380":"1380","1429":"1429","Glassenbury, Kent, England":"Glassenbury, Kent, England","Maidstone, Kent, England":"Maidstone, Kent, England","England":"England"},"fr":{"1355–1380":"1355–1380","1340–1399":"1340–1399","1375–1429":"1375–1429","–Male":"Décédé","2 April 1375":"2 avril 1375","1355":"1355","1399":"1399","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","1380":"1380","1429":"1429","Glassenbury, Kent, England":"Glassenbury, Kent, Angleterre","Maidstone, Kent, England":"Maidstone, Kent, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lady Katherine de Buckfold est née en 1355, à Angleterre, fille de de Buckfold. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Sir John Beale. Elle est décédée en 1380, à Glassenbury, Kent, Angleterre, à l’âge de 25 ans."},"de":{"1355–1380":"1355–1380","13